Author:  FORSTER
Vol / Page:  2/300
Edition:
Quote:  Next to this comes the <i>Maheepehh</i> [a-macron, e2-grave, e3-cupped, h2-inferior circumflex^], a wooden battle Ax; it has a curved point like a hallbeard & below it has the shape of a paddle. [ed. fn Possibly <i>maipi </i>which, according to Elsdon best, is synonymous with <i>taiaha</i>, long straight club; the description seems to fit <i>tewhatewha</i>, a battle-axe shaped weapon.
